# [JOSE](../wg/jose.html)

**IETF 125 Session Minutes**

## Summary
The JOSE working group met at IETF 125 to discuss the progress of JSON Web Proofs, post-quantum cryptography (PQC) integration, and algorithm deprecation. Key highlights included the introduction of Michael Jones as the new co-chair, the progression of several drafts toward Working Group Last Call (WGLC), and a significant discussion regarding the coordination of post-quantum algorithm registrations between JOSE and COSE.

## Key Discussion Points

### Administrative and Document Status
*   **Chair Transition:** Karen O'Donoghue introduced Michael Jones as the new co-chair, succeeding John Mattsson. Deb Cooley remains the Area Director (AD).
*   **HPKE Status:** The HPKE document has been forwarded to the IESG.
*   **Algorithm Deprecation:** [draft-ietf-jose-deprecate-none-rsa15](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-jose-deprecate-none-rsa15/) has been updated to reflect consensus on wording. The chairs will move this document to Working Group Last Call.

### JSON Web Proof (JWP)
**Presentation:** [JSON Web Proof Update](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-jose-json-web-proof-update-03)
**Presenters:** Mike Jones, David Waite

*   **Algorithm Identifiers:** To avoid conflict with the JWA/COSE registries, a new `proof-alg` identifier was introduced for use in keys.
*   **Selective Disclosure:** Discussion on whether to add functionality similar to SD-JWT to allow disclosing parts of a claim (e.g., specific fields in an address). 
*   **BBS Extensions:** Discussion regarding BBS Blind Signatures and Per-Verifier Identifiers. Brent Zundell and John Bradley noted that blind signatures are core to BBS use cases (e.g., European digital identity). The authors will likely keep these in a separate draft for now to avoid delaying the core JWP specifications: [draft-ietf-jose-json-web-proof](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-jose-json-web-proof/), [draft-ietf-jose-json-proof-token](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-jose-json-proof-token/), and [draft-ietf-jose-json-proof-algorithms](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-jose-json-proof-algorithms/).

### Post-Quantum Key Encapsulation Mechanisms (PQ KEMs)
**Presentation:** [PQ KEMs for COSE AND JOSE](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-jose-pq-kems-for-cose-and-jose-00)
**Presenter:** Tirumaleswar Reddy

*   **Draft Status:** [draft-ietf-jose-pqc-kem](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-jose-pqc-kem/) was updated to use AKB (Algorithm Key Basket) based on previous consensus.
*   **HPKE vs. Direct KEM:** A debate ensued regarding the necessity of this draft given the availability of HPKE. Mike Jones and Jaroslav Resler questioned the need for two ways to perform PQC key agreement. John Bradley and Tirumaleswar Reddy argued that direct KEM support provides a simpler migration path for constrained environments (like the LAKE working group) that do not require the full HPKE suite.
*   **Consensus Path:** The chairs will take the discussion to the mailing list to determine if there is a compelling use case for a non-HPKE PQC mechanism in JOSE before proceeding to WGLC.

### PQ/T Hybrid Composite Signatures
**Presentation:** [PQ/T Hybrid Composite Signatures for JOSE and COSE](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-jose-pqt-hybrid-composite-signatures-for-jose-and-cose-00)
**Presenter:** Philip Lafrance

*   **Draft Update:** [draft-ietf-jose-pq-composite-sigs](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-jose-pq-composite-sigs/) was updated with new test vectors and expanded security considerations regarding existential unforgeability (EUF-CMA).
*   **Feedback:** The WG was asked to review the list of registered algorithms to ensure it is appropriately scoped.

### JOSE HPKE PQC and PQ/T Algorithm Registrations
**Presentations:** 
*   [JOSE HPKE PQ & PQ/T Algorithm Registrations](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-jose-jose-hpke-pq-pqt-algorithm-registrations-01) (Philip Lafrance)
*   [Post-Quantum and Hybrid KEMs for HPKE with JOSE and COSE](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-jose-post-quantum-and-hybrid-kems-for-hpke-with-jose-and-cose-00) (Tirumaleswar Reddy)

*   **Competing Approaches:** Two drafts cover the registration of PQC algorithms for HPKE. One (Lafrance/Campbell) focuses strictly on JOSE registrations and automated test vectors; the other (Reddy/Tschofenig) covers both JOSE and COSE and includes more normative guidance on transition paths and security properties.
*   **Algorithm Trimming:** There was general agreement to reduce optionality. Proposed changes include removing ChaCha20-Poly1305 for JOSE key encryption (as it is not standard in JWE) and potentially removing ML-KEM-512 for JOSE.
*   **JOSE/COSE Alignment:** Brian Campbell argued for keeping the JOSE work separate to avoid "shackling" the two groups together when their requirements diverge (e.g., constrained device needs in COSE vs. web needs in JOSE). Mike Jones and Hannes Tschofenig advocated for alignment where core functionality overlaps.

## Decisions and Action Items
*   **Decision:** [draft-ietf-jose-deprecate-none-rsa15](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-jose-deprecate-none-rsa15/) will move to Working Group Last Call.
*   **Action Item:** The authors of the two HPKE PQC registration drafts (Philip Lafrance, Brian Campbell, Tirumaleswar Reddy, and Hannes Tschofenig) are directed by the AD and Chairs to meet and consolidate their work.
*   **Action Item:** The discussion regarding the necessity of [draft-ietf-jose-pqc-kem](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-jose-pqc-kem/) (direct KEM) versus HPKE-only PQC will be moved to the mailing list.

## Next Steps
1.  Initiate WGLC for the deprecation draft.
2.  Authors to coordinate on a unified HPKE PQC registration document (or a clear split between JOSE and COSE documents).
3.  Working group members to review [draft-ietf-jose-pq-composite-sigs](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-jose-pq-composite-sigs/) and provide feedback on the algorithm list.